239 (d)(1) The above appropriation for teacher professional
240 development shall be allocated to the Alabama Department of
241 Education to be distributed to the Ed Farm Classroom of
242 Tomorrow. These funds will be used by Ed Farm to provide
243 technology tools and professional development services to
244 classroom teachers in an effort to improve instruction and
245 student learning gains. It is the intent of the legislature
246 that in addition to general programmatic costs, Ed Farm may
247 also expend funds for software, hardware, administrative
248 costs, and professional learning services.
249 (2) The State Superintendent shall provide a report of the
250 initiative to the Chair of the House Ways and Means-Education
251 Committee and the Chair of the Senate Committee on Finance and
252 Taxation-Education no later than October 1, 2027.
