302 Section 4. (a) Notwithstanding the provisions of Section
303 29-9-4, Code of Alabama 1975, and in addition to all other
304 appropriations heretofore or hereafter made, there is hereby
305 appropriated a total of $150,000,000 from the Education Trust
Page 12

appropriated a total of $150,000,000 from the Education Trust
NRYWNJJ-1 03/31/2026 KHF (F) KHF FINANCE AND TAXATION EDUCATION
SUBSTITUTE TO HB236 2026-1428
306 Fund Advancement and Technology Fund to the Department of
307 Education to provide matching grants to local education
308 agencies for expenses related to developing regional career
309 technology centers throughout the state, including capital
310 outlay and equipment, for the fiscal year ending September 30,
311 2026. Grant proposals shall be submitted by a collaboration of
312 at least two local education agencies or between a local
313 education agency partnering with a community college within
314 the Alabama Community College System. Should a local education
315 agency partner with a community college, the local education
316 agency shall maintain full control of the grant from the
317 Department of Education.
318 (b) The State Superintendent of Education shall appoint a
319 committee to review and recommend grant proposals for
320 approval. The State Superintendent of Education shall utilize
321 a sliding scale of matching requirements for grant proposals,
322 taking into consideration the financial capacity of the
323 eligible local education agencies to provide matching funds,
324 so long as the required match does not exceed 50 percent of
325 the total cost of the project. The State Superintendent of
326 Education shall give preference in awarding grants pursuant to
327 this section to grant proposals from local education agencies
328 that were not awarded the full amount of grant funds requested
329 pursuant to Act 2025-269, and to grant proposals from local
Page 13

pursuant to Act 2025-269, and to grant proposals from local
NRYWNJJ-1 03/31/2026 KHF (F) KHF FINANCE AND TAXATION EDUCATION
SUBSTITUTE TO HB236 2026-1428
330 education agencies that submitted applications for grant funds
331 pursuant Act 2025-269 but did not receive a grant. However,
332 the total amount of grant funds that may be awarded for the
333 same project shall not exceed $20,000,000 for all grant years.
334 (c) The State Superintendent of Education shall notify
335 each local superintendent and finance officer of each local
336 education agency by email regarding the availability and
337 application process of grants to be awarded pursuant to this
338 section, including any required forms. The State
339 Superintendent shall notify all members of the local
340 legislative delegation five days prior to the announcement of
341 any grant made to any entity located in the legislative
342 jurisdiction. The five days prior notice requirement shall be
343 waived in the event of a declared emergency. The Governor
344 shall encourage the Department to disburse the funds provided
345 herein on a nondiscriminatory basis.
346 Section 5. All funds appropriated herein and not
347 expended in the current fiscal year shall not revert but be
348 carried forward for the purpose appropriated.
349 Section 6. This act shall become effective immediately
350 following its passage and approval by the Governor, or its
351 otherwise becoming law.
